Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting possible acute or chronic kidney dysfunction with protein loss and ketone production. HbA1c is low, making chronic hyperglycemia unlikely. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation for renal impairment and further assessment of underlying etiology.
